From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ASK2 PR14c-body-2 <ask2@vyos.local>
Date: Wed, 14 May 2026 04:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fman/pcd/cc: node create/destroy bodies (PR14c-body-2)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

PR14c-body-2 of the ASK2 v1.0 PR14 series.  Replaces the PR14c-prep
-EOPNOTSUPP stubs for fman_pcd_cc_node_create() and
fman_pcd_cc_node_destroy() with real MURAM-resident match-key record
+ AD-table allocation per LS1046A RM 8.7.4.2 and 8.7.4.3.  Tree
create/destroy bodies landed in PR14c-body-1 (patch 0009).  The
remaining two stubs (fman_pcd_cc_node_add_key,
_modify_next_action) stay stubbed; they land in PR14c-body-4 once
the action-encoding helper from PR14c-body-3 is available.

Spec design memo: plans/ASK2-IMPLEMENTATION.md "PR14c-body design
memo" section, committed in 537a008.

Silicon facts (RM 8.7.4.2 + 8.7.4.3, cross-ref SDK fm_cc.h/fm_cc.c)
------------------------------------------------------------------
  - Per-node match-key record is (num_keys + 1) rows; each row is
    (key + mask), extract.size bytes each.  Trailing row is the
    miss slot per RM 8.7.4.2 paragraph 5.  Table base 16-B aligned.
  - AD table is (num_keys + 1) * 16 bytes; entry [i] is the AD for
    key [i], last entry (index num_keys) is the miss-AD per
    RM 8.7.4.3 paragraph 3.  Table base 16-B aligned.
  - extract.size is 1..56 bytes (silicon hard limit, RM 8.7.4.2
    Table 8-118; cross-ref SDK fm_cc.h FM_PCD_CC_KEY_MAX_SIZE).
  - num_keys is 0..255 (cross-ref SDK fm_cc.h:175
    FM_PCD_CC_NUM_OF_KEYS = 255).
  - fman_muram_alloc()'s gen_pool min_alloc_order = 8 satisfies the
    16-B RM alignment naturally.

Implementation
--------------
  - struct fman_pcd_cc_node definition added (private to this TU;
    public ABI forward-declares it).  Fields: list anchor on
    tree->nodes, back-pointers (tree, pcd), copied extract spec,
    MURAM offsets + iomem pointers for match and AD tables, table
    sizes for free, in-memory keys mirror, num_keys/max_keys,
    spinlock for add_key/modify (body-4).
  - fman_pcd_cc_node_create(): validates args (extract.size 1..56,
    num_keys 0..255), kzalloc the handle, fman_pcd_muram_alloc()
    both tables (budget-accounted), fman_muram_offset_to_vbase()
    for CPU pointers, memset_io() both to zero (silicon walker
    sees "no match" until PR14c-body-3 lands the encoder),
    kcalloc the in-memory keys mirror, list_add under
    tree->lifecycle_lock.
  - fman_pcd_cc_node_destroy(): list_del under tree->lifecycle_lock,
    kfree the mirror, free both MURAM tables in reverse order,
    kfree the handle.  No WARN_ON needed: silicon CCBS binding is
    at tree granularity, not node granularity, so there is no
    caller-leak signal at this layer.

Validation (native ARM64 build on Cobalt 100)
---------------------------------------------
  - make ARCH=arm64 -j32 drivers/net/.../fman_pcd_cc.o: success,
    zero warnings, zero errors.
  - make ARCH=arm64 -j32 Image modules: success, vmlinux links.
  - nm fman_pcd_cc.o: fman_pcd_cc_node_create grew 28 -> 288 B
    (0x120), fman_pcd_cc_node_destroy grew 24 -> 1016 B (0x3f8).
    The two remaining node stubs (_add_key, _modify_next_action)
    unchanged at 8 B and 48 B (0x30).  All six __ksymtab_* entries
    present.

References
----------
  specs/ask2-rewrite-spec.md sec 13.3 (fman_pcd_cc.c LOC budget)
  specs/ask2-rewrite-spec.md sec 16 (provenance discipline v1.1)
  plans/ASK2-IMPLEMENTATION.md PR14c-body design memo (537a008)
  LS1046A Reference Manual sec 8.7.4.2 (CC node match-key record)
  LS1046A Reference Manual sec 8.7.4.3 (action template encoding)

Signed-off-by: ASK2 PR14c-body-2 <ask2@vyos.local>
